title.64: Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual (1979) #3

description.0: The Fantastic Four travel to Seaboard University so testing can be conducted on Franklin and his powers. Meanwhile at a Massachusetts bar, Johnny goes overboard to impress Lorrie Melton...and messes with the wrong guy!
description.1: Spider-Man battles Gideon and his foot soldiers, who have wounded the White Tiger, Spidey's ally.
description.7: The Rebels encounter a prototype of a new probe droid that is as deadly as any fighter!
description.9: Thanks to the Wizard, Spider-Man must rescue the tenants of his building from a burning rooftop. But passed-out Wino Charlie wasn't aware of the danger! Can Spider-Man save himself, and Charlie, from a certain, fiery death?
description.10: Dr. Liu, the Yellow Claw's assistant, comes to Avengers Mansion to warn the team about Claw's ulterior motives. Liu is promptly killed by remote control before he can utter more than a set of coordinates. The Vision remains at the mansion to recuperate, while the rest of the team investigates Liu's coordinates in the Australian desert.
description.11: It's the 40th anniversary of Captain America! Join Cap and his comrades down memory lane, and witness the legend that is Captain America!
description.13: In an effort to fulfill her dream of becoming a singer, Dazzler responds to a wanted ad at a disco venue. Meanwhile, The Enchantress learns about a dimensional rift that will occur at that same venue...and has a full Disco Diva Battle with Daz!
description.16: Eternity has sent three portions of himself out into the universe so that they may understand mortal life- but now they don't want to come back! Can the Defenders bring back the pieces of Eternity before their absence causes the universe to end?
description.19: After the Daily Globe releases a story about Strange, one of its editors becomes very intrigued by the Doctor and decides to learn more…
description.23: The conclusion of the adaptation of The Empire Strikes Back!  Vader and Luke finally square off!
description.27: The She-Witch of Doom! Can the Ghost Rider keep his soul or will he enter a new waking hell at the hands of a demon?
description.28: Hulk finds himself in the crossfire of the Israelis and the Arabs! Will Banner's compassion for a fallen child soften Sabra's heart?
description.29: Iron Man faces Sunturion in a deadly space duel.
description.32: A woman's life is at risk when the Wrecking Crew escapes from prison. Will Thor lend a hand? Meanwhile, Dr. Donald Blake applies to the West Side Medical Clinic.
description.33: A mortal woman causes battle between Asgardian gods! Complicating matters? The main combatants are father and son! Thor and Odin duke it out for the love of Jane Foster- and the Avengers are also thrown into the fray!
description.34: The team takes a vacation in Pennsylvania...but is still faced with some odd run-ins. Meanwhile, mysterious egg-parasites are discovered below a lake's surface.
description.35: The text on the front cover says it all: "This issue: Everbody dies!" With Chris Claremont and John Byrne's team-up coming to an end, they went all out to conclude "Days of Future Past," the ultimate time-travel, everything's gone wrong tales.
description.36: Aliens and Illusions! Spidey must take down Mysterio who has kidnapped Aunt May, her new fianc', and Debra Whitman!
description.37: The Wizard escapes from Ryker's Island...and he makes it look easy! Who is Wizard's mysterious co-conspirator? Spider-Man is active on the scene of a subway collapse, and Debra pushes for the next step in her and Peter's relationship. Will Spider-Man be able to juggle the crises of city living, and the crisis of his heart?
description.38: The Avengers answer a distress call from a woman named Shu Han. Han is being kept on an isolated and fortified island, where she is the captive of the villainous Yellow Claw!
description.39: Captain America faces a vampiric foe known as Baron Blood. Can the Sentinel of Liberty overcome his mesmerizing powers before Baron Blood sinks his fangs into him?
description.40: Spidey takes on The Punisher in an incredible showdown!
description.43: This issue reveals that Matt Murdock loved Elektra before his accident and the murder of her parents. Seeking a different path for her solace, Elektra has turned to the bloody justice of the Hand.
description.45: Ghost Rider runs afoul of the recently freed Sirens of Kronos. Can Ghost Rider send them back to their imprisonment or will he fall under their spell?
description.46: Hulk vs. Thor in a battle across New York City! Banner decides to embark on a long journey.
description.47: Mike Trudeau hijacks the Jupiter Landing Vehicle and Iron Man must stop him.
description.48: Ghost Rider's battle continues! Thinking the villainous Snake Dance is defeated, Blaze then comes face-to-face with the WITCH-WOMAN!
description.49: Spider-Woman faces a villian who is a real blast from the past!
description.50: Thor helps a priest save his church from mobsters!
description.51: Old man Wolverine? Adult Kitty Pryde? Dead and captured X-Men? John Byrne spun fans around with this terrifying and captivating cover.
description.52: The Samurai Destroyer is plundering riches around the world. The Fantastic Four along with the Shogun Warriors must travel to Japan to face it- but will the robot's true origins destroy the future of the Shogun Warriors?
description.53: An alien invasion is underway! Spider-Man's dinner is interrupted by extraterrestrial waiters working for an old foe.
description.57: Hydro-Man's first appearance! During a New York City heatwave, Morris Bench is transformed into a being of water. Hydro-Man blames Spider-Man for this phenomenon, and he's traveling through sewers, hoses, sinks, and showers to find the wall-crawler responsible! Spider-Man vs. his most unusual villain yet!
description.58: The first appearance of Rogue! Ms. Marvel lies disoriented and weakened after her powers are absorbed by Rogue. Will Spider-Woman be able to restore her amnesiac friend? Just as the Avengers band together to take care of their fallen teammate, the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants attack!
description.59: The Beast and Wonder Man search for a young boy named Hugo Lopez in the New York City sewers. Turns out, young Hugo has befriended a group of "Crawlers"; worm-like creatures formed from the remains of anaerobic mutation research. Beast and Wonder Man encourage Hugo to leave behind his sewer friends.
description.60: When a serial killer runs loose in northern London, Captain America must confront a monster from his past.
description.62: The Empire Strikes Back adaptation continues as their a betrayal at Bespin!
description.65: The usually brawny Thor must exercise intellect and restraint when Umar manipulates him into playing a game of chess with Dormammu! Should either side win, Asgard will be plunged into hellfire!
description.66: Impending nuclear doom is coming, and neither the Hulk, nor Bruce Banner, are great enough to prevent it. But what if both of their strengths are put together by a mysterious force...?
description.69: As Hellcat fights the mind-controlled Valkyrie, the rest of the Defenders race to stop Mandrill from overloading a nuclear reactor. Things only get more complicated when it’s revealed who works at the nuclear facility and how they’re connected to the mind-controlling mutant!
description.76: Ghost Rider finds himself at the mercy of an angry trucker. Plus, the return of the Night Rider!
description.77: Hulk accidentally foils the plan of four villains attempting to have a Fantastic Four-like transformation.
description.78: After modifying his armor to go after the submarine with Bethany Cabe aboard, Tony engages Force in underwater combat!
description.80: First Spider-Woman had to face The Hornet and now she has to fight Werewolf by Night!
description.81: While all of Asgard celebrates, Balder remains bitter about past sorrows. Meanwhile, can Donald Blake reestablish a life back on Earth?
description.82: What if Gwen Stacy had not only lived, but had also learned Spider-Man's secret identity? Peter and Gwen, united in holy matrimony! But how long can this newfound peace last? If J. Jonah Jameson has any say in the matter...not long at all!
description.83: Reed has saved the life of Korgon! But just as fast as he's been revived, Korgon goes mad and uses the Darkfield Rod on the FF, stripping them of their powers!
description.84: Spidey has his first brush with the dastardly Smuggler. The White Tiger returns.
description.92: It's the next chapter of The Empire Strikes Back adaptation as Luke meets Yoda and starts his Jedi training.
description.93: Spider-Man must quell the anger of Namor the Sub-Mariner, after two divers invade his Atlantean realm. Is Spidey up to this difficult task? Plus, Debra appeals to Peter on behalf of her sickly uncle. But how are her uncle's current woes connected to Namor?
description.94: After adamantium resins go missing from Stark's power plant and Pym's laboratory, the Avengers fear the return of Ultron.
description.95: Captain America battles both Batrok and Mr. Hyde in this blockbuster issue! Don't miss out!
description.97: Spider-Man and the Fantastic Four are unwilling heroes to a new mutant, a young woman who claims her siblings are in danger under her uncle's care.
description.98: Doctor Strange battles Shialmar, the Shadow Queen. A gigantic, mystical bolt strikes and only will survive.
description.99: Mandrill makes a mess of things during the Nighthawk's court appearance with his army of mind-controlled women! Will Daredevil, The Hulk and Nighthawk be able to save the day?

2.text: A newlywed couple and their baby encounter danger deep in the Everglades swamps…

3.text: Shang-Chi vs. the Shadow-Slasher! Is the Master of Kung Fu’s opponent the best at what he does?

8.text: Featuring Black Widow in her own black and white adventure!

12.text: Cosmic hero Quasar joins the Thing in battle against prehistoric beasts!

14.text: Moon Knight, avatar of Khonshu, in the trenches of the supernatural! After tracking down a criminally insane man, Moon Knight enters his haunted house. What terrors lie within?

15.text: Jennifer Walters is tormented by bad dreams stemming from painful past memories.

16.text: Eternity has sent three portions of himself out into the universe so that they may understand mortal life- but now they don't want to come back! Can the Defenders bring back the pieces of Eternity before their absence causes the universe to end?

17.text: The Inhuman Royal Family experiences the true terror of Maelstrom! And Maelstrom has backup!

20.text: Bushmaster kidnaps Luke Cage after discovering a way to reverse his powers! Iron Fist must solve his partner’s disappearance and save Power Man before any experiment is conducted. Iron Fist vs. Weird Science!

21.text: It's the witching hour at Delmar Insurance, as Machine Man plays security guard at a Halloween party! But when the maniacal Jack O'Lantern crashes the scene, guests must endure more tricks than treats!

22.text: Someone or something is on Moon Knight’s trail, and they won’t stop until he’s cold in the ground! The Committee of Five Assassins regroups, and their first hit is Moon Knight!

24.text: Shang-Chi’s dinner party hits an unexpected snag when a gang of thieves crashes the scene!

27.text: The She-Witch of Doom! Can the Ghost Rider keep his soul or will he enter a new waking hell at the hands of a demon?

35.text: In the present, the X-Men fight against the Brotherhood of Mutants. In the future, they battle the deadly mutant-killing Sentinels. And linking these two worlds, these two desperate battles, is Katherine Pryde. The fate of mutantkind is in her hands!

The text on the front cover says it all: "This issue: Everbody dies!" With Chris Claremont and John Byrne's team-up coming to an end, they went all out to conclude "Days of Future Past," the ultimate time-travel, everything's gone wrong tales.

40.text: Spidey takes on The Punisher in an incredible showdown!

41.text: Morbius the Living Vampire has the antidote to She-Hulk's condition, but this is a case of too little, too late!

42.text: The X-Men versus the hordes of the Badoon! When a galactic threat looms over the merry mutants, the team calls in the aid of experts- the Fantastic Four! Meanwhile, Storm can’t shake her feelings for Arkon, and her need to end the battles in his home world. Can the X-Men and the Fantastic Four usher in an age of peace between two warring alien races?

44.text: At a tavern, the Thing sees a man whose been shot stumble and collapse into the place! Who is this man, why is he being chased, and can the Fantastic Four help him?

45.text: Ghost Rider runs afoul of the recently freed Sirens of Kronos. Can Ghost Rider send them back to their imprisonment or will he fall under their spell?

51.text: Journey into the dystopian future  - where Sentinels stalk the Earth, and the X-Men are humanity's only hope...until they die!
Old man Wolverine? Adult Kitty Pryde? Dead and captured X-Men? John Byrne spun fans around with this terrifying and captivating cover.

61.text: On three consecutive nights, Moon Knight apprehends three criminals at the same time. As if that weren’t coincidence enough, each criminal has stolen a valuable item related to each other. Moon Knight vs. the Midnight Man!

64.text: Featuring the startling final fate of the Man-Wolf!

67.text: Maelstrom makes their Marvel debut! Mister Fantastic and the Thing face off against a new foe after their visit to the Inhumans’ Great Refuge.

68.text: Nighthawk and Spider-Man head to Grayburn Unviersity, Nighthawk's alma mater! It's exactly like he remembers - a little TOO exact! An old ghost from Kyle Richmond's past returns to haunt him in this homecoming horror show!

70.text: It’s up to Man-Thing to rescue Sheriff Daltry and Barbie Bannister from Captain Fate and his derelict crew!

71.text: The C.I.A. twist Shang-Chi’s arm into helping them on a mission with Agent Carter.

74.text: Wendigo continues to wreck havok and its up to Alpha Flight and the X-Men to bring the beast down. And introducing the New Brotherhood of Evil Mutants.

75.text: The normally invincible She-Hulk is weakened by a sickness that threatens to claim her life!

76.text: Ghost Rider finds himself at the mercy of an angry trucker. Plus, the return of the Night Rider!

85.text: Sir Denis Nayland Smith launches a freelance operation.

89.text: The Daughters of the Dragon are in need of Power Man and Iron Fist’s help! A group of thieves led by Sabretooth and Constrictor have stolen the Jade Tiger and ensnared Misty Knight! Our two heroes enter the vault…but may wish they hadn’t!

90.text: Machine Man is detained by the Canadian authorities following a Hulk debacle. Alpha Flight guest-stars!

91.text: In the dark alleys of New York, Moon Knight hunts for the “Skid Row Slasher.” Later, Spector takes on the guise of sophisticated Steven Grant, and attempts to find information about the killer from a newspaper publisher.

96.text: Ben Grimm takes the next step in his relationship with Alicia Masters, but things hit a snag when Shellshock attacks!
